3 years , 3 pregnancies, 3 semesters off due to medical reason & I finally graduated from nursing school! Wouldn't have been able to do it without Gods grace & strength as well as my amazing husband (thanks for always being my shoulder) & my parents. They stood by me, encouraged me & most importantly never allowed me to believe that I would never be able to finish. I learned that although I wanted to be at others pace, I needed to stay in my lane & let my journey take its course. All I can say is that everyone's journey is different & it doesn't make it any less special if anything it becomes more valuable & makes you work harder. Thanks to those who have kept me in their prayers & sent me encouragement during this journey, it will never be forgotten. BUT This is for my kids = your momma made it ❤
